The paper discusses the performance of algorithms in comparison to human experts, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the decision of which instances of a task to give to an algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the role of human judgment in automation, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the importance of error estimation, which is relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
